column4: "The first 8 bars of the A section lend themselves to a single scale  approach (=modal). Several approaches work well:\012"

"* An  A  phrygian scale. (Over the A chord use the notes of  F major scale. For chords to accompany play an A7b9sus4 chord. (A Bb D E G) or perhaps Bb/A or Em7b5/A - or string together a series of diatonic chords from the   F major scale.\012"
"*  half tone/whole tone diminished scale. For chords over the A chord play any dominant type chords from this scale (E.g  A13 or  A7#9
column5: or C13  or C7#9 or Eb13 or Eb7#9 or F#13 or F#7b9 - or string together a series of chords from the diminished scale.\012"
